JD 1:

Key Responsibilities:Marketplace Management:
Manage listings, content, A+ pages, and SEO for platforms like Amazon, Flipkart, and Nykaa
Run platform campaigns and promotions, coordinate with account managers
Optimize pricing, discounts, and margins to maximize ROI
Track and analyze weekly sales, inventory, RTOs, and returns
Quick Commerce Management:
Lead SKU curation for platforms like Blinkit, Zepto, and Instamart
Coordinate onboarding of products with appropriate pack sizes and inventory sync
Monitor OTIF (On-Time In-Full), stock fill rates, and out-of-stock rates
Ensure TAT (Turnaround Time), delivery performance, and price parity across platforms
Performance Metrics:
Revenue and GMV growth per channel
Fill Rate, OTIF, RTO%, and Inventory Days of Stock (DOS)
Ad spends vs ROAS (in sync with performance team)
Platform scorecard maintenance (Amazon/Nykaa health scores)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JD 2:

Key Responsibilities

1.

Category Ownership & Strategy

Own and drive fulfillment category P&L metrics, including cost per order, delivery success rate, and RTO impact.
Define and execute category strategy to scale order volumes while balancing cost, speed, and service quality.
Build and execute short-term and long-term roadmaps for fulfillment capacity expansion, geography coverage, and efficiency improvements.
2.

Operations & Execution

Own the entire fulfillment lifecycle: order processing → picking/packing → shipping → last-mile delivery → returns.
Ensure high SLA adherence across warehousing, courier, and last-mile partners.
Design, document, and implement SOPs to support rapid growth, seasonal spikes, and peak demand periods.
3.

Vendor & Partner Management

Own and manage courier, 3PL, and warehouse partnerships.
Negotiate commercial terms, SLAs, and performance benchmarks aligned with category goals.
Drive partner accountability through regular reviews, data-backed performance tracking, and continuous improvement initiatives.
4.

Inventory, Returns & Customer Experience Impact

Ensure inventory accuracy and availability across fulfillment locations.
Own returns, RTOs, and reverse logistics performance, working to reduce costs and improve recovery rates.
Collaborate closely with CX and Sales teams to identify, reduce, and prevent delivery-related customer issues.
5.

Data, Metrics & Optimization

Track, analyze, and optimize key fulfillment metrics, including:
Fulfillment TAT
Cost per shipment
Delivery success rate
RTO and return rates
Use data to identify bottlenecks, inefficiencies, and root causes, and drive automation and process improvements.
Continuously improve margins and service quality through data-driven decisions.
6.

Team & Stakeholder Management

Build, manage, and scale fulfillment operations teams in line with category growth.
Work cross-functionally with Tech, Product, Finance, CX, and Sales teams to deliver category objectives.
Present category performance, insights, and growth plans to senior leadership.

