JD 36:

Key Responsibilities

1. Category Growth & P&L Ownership

Own GMV, net revenue, margins, sell-through, and inventory turns for the category
Drive profitable growth across D2C, marketplaces, retail, and quick commerce
Identify growth levers by channel, region, price band, and product type


2. Demand Forecasting & Supply Alignment

Own SKU-level and style-level demand forecasts
Work with BI to translate historical sales, seasonality, and trends into forecasts
Partner with supply planning to:
Avoid stock-outs on winners
Control excess inventory on slow movers
Continuously improve forecast accuracy through learning loops


3. Pricing, Discounting & Margin Strategy

Define pricing architecture by:
Channel
Region
Occasion & season
Plan discounting strategy across full price, events, clearance, and end-of-season
Balance growth vs margin while maintaining brand positioning


4. New Launch & Range Planning

Plan season-wise launch calendars in collaboration with design and supply
Define:
Number of styles
Depth per style
Size and color mix
Track new launch performance and activate early reorders or corrections


5. Customer & Market Understanding (Core Differentiator)

Develop a deep understanding of the category customer:
Who they are
Why they buy from Kisah
Price sensitivity
Regional preferences
Occasion-led demand
Analyze returns, cancellations, and customer feedback to identify product gaps
Translate customer insights into actionable product and pricing decisions


6. Seasonal & Campaign Planning

Own category-level planning for:
Key festivals
Micro-events (Eid, Rakhi, Onam, wedding season, etc.)
Clearance & liquidation events
Work with growth, marketing, and merchandising teams to ensure:
Right assortment
Right pricing
Right inventory availability


7. Cross-Functional Collaboration

Work closely with:
BI – for data enablement and forecasting
Design – for product inputs and range correction
Supply Chain – for production planning and replenishment
Growth & Merchandising – for visibility and conversion
Act as the single point of accountability for category performance

